OL,4,CEngland's independence
OL,6,FThe 44 MPs included former Tory leader
OL,7,FSir Iain Duncan Smith, former cabinet
OL,8,Fministers Sir Jacob Rees-Mogg, Sir
OL,9,FGavin Williamson, Suella Braverman and
OL,10,FRobert Jenrick, and other backbenchers
OL,11,Fseen as being on the right of the
OL,12,Fparty.
OL,14,FSir Jacob accused the Bank of
OL,15,F"miserable incompetence" that made
OL,16,FNick Leeson, the rogue trader who
OL,17,Fbankrupted Barings Bank in 1995, "look
OL,18,Fclever".
